column5: They aren't steelhead, but there's also no crowds.
A really nice spot you have there.  Thanks for the pics.

lakers or splake?  definitely nice country up there, looks like more fun to me rather than fishing shoulder to shoulder down here  I'm guessing the ponds might get a skim of ice in the next couple days up there  PM me if you're ever looking for company to hit some back lakes
The yr-round lakers and splakers have been chompin' last week or two!  Once this cold snap lets go there should be another good week of action coming up before the big lockup!
lucky not a soul in sight
Lovely. I would not mind the scenery and some tranquility.  Thanks for sharing

lakers or splake?  definitely nice country up there, looks like more fun to me rather than fishing shoulder to shoulder down here  I'm guessing the ponds might get a skim of ice in the next couple days up there  PM me if you're ever looking for company to hit some back lakes Splake. This is a great time of year for them, and they will be biting until it freezes over.
